questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application experiences a progressive slowdown, eventually crashing with `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`. Analyzing the heap dump reveals millions of `byte[]` instances retained by `java.lang.Thread` objects in the Tomcat worker thread pool. Here is the service implementation:

java
@Service
public class TransactionalReportService {
    private final ThreadLocal<byte[]> processingBuffer = ThreadLocal.withInitial(() -> new byte[5 * 1024 * 1024]); // 5MB

    @Transactional(readOnly = true)
    public void processReport(UUID reportId) {
        byte[] buffer = processingBuffer.get();
        fillReportData(buffer, reportId);
        // Processing logic occurs here...
    }

    private void fillReportData(byte[] buffer, UUID id) {}
}
